TechNexus SCITI – Smart Cities Internet of Things Innovation Smart City IoT Innovation (SCITI) Labs (pronounced ‘CITY’) is a smart city solutions innovation lab created in collaboration between the US Department of Homeland Security, CIT, TechNexus, and Smart City Get Involved SCITI Labs Mission Collaboratively develop solutions designed to support First Responders’ capabilities in the Smart City environment, by providing technologies with market access, development capital, and aligning those technologies with larger tangential opportunities in broader Capital We are actively looking for innovators developing technology directly aligned with the mission of First Responders and or are in related industries (e.g. Smart Cities). Innovator Collaboration SCITI Labs brings together entrepreneurs, industry partners, technologists, investors, and public sector influencers working in concert to actively advance breakthrough Selected innovators will be eligible to receive capital for Prototype Testing Solutions apart of the SCITI Labs program are evaluated on their ability meet the core technology requirements (provided by DHS), but also by their application and commercial viability in adjacent Commercialization A final group of innovators will be selected to receive capital and work with first responders and technology experts to define and accelerate their with government and corporate Focus Areas Smart HUB (Communication Interoperability Platform) Learn More UAS Unmanned Aerial Systems & Optical Sensors Learn More Smart City Smart Building Sensor Suite Learn More Apply below to get started with Apply About TechNexus TechNexus is collaborating with DHS & CIT to provide capital and venture development opportunities to early stage We align startups and enterprises to drive commercial activity that solves real world Venture collaboration improves the reach, speed and effectiveness of Learn More Contact Us Start typing and press Enter to search

for use on humans   About — ClearCam Home About Press Contact Home About Press Contact about us In John Uecker, a General Surgeon at Seton Medical, approached Chris Rylander, a professor at the University of Texas at Austin Cockrell School of Engineering, with a problem that he felt had no effective Uecker performed about laparoscopic surgeries a year and was incredibly frustrated by having to constantly clean the laparoscopic During the course of a laparoscopic procedure he would have to break concentration, remove the camera from the patient s body, clean the camera, and then the scope into the patient and find his position to resume the Uecker believed that longer surgeries, greater patient risk, higher cost, and surgical frustration had to have a When Rylander understood the problem he also felt it was worth solving and, with the help of PhD candidate Chris Idelson, set his lab into The goal was to create a simple, compatible cleaner that would effectively deal with the main culprits of camera visual blood, tissue, fat, and After over a year of development Rylander and Idelson had their initial product and Uecker began testing In the fall of the IP was patented and Doug Stoakley, an Entrepreneurial Advisor with the Innovation Center at the UT School of Engineering and longtime technology executive, joined ClearCam to drive operations, fundraising, and business One important sign to watch for is forgetfulness, especially when it pertains to newly learned In normal cases of aging, it’s easy to forget details of appointments and schedules but remember them later However, in the case of Alzheimer’s or dementia, forgetfulness of a detail (especially when the information is repeated over and over again) is an early sign of the Another sign to look for is difficulty completing everyday activities such as remembering directions to a familiar location or keeping track of Why Are Memory Homes Important For Those With Alzheimers or Dementia? Memory care homes are specially designed for residents to feel comfortable and safe in a familiar The facility is supervised 7, assuring family members that each resident will be safe and cared Structured routines and programs help residents maintain a healthy and balanced lifestyle while minimizing the risks of wandering These designated facilities have trained staff members specializing in Alzheimer’s disease and dementia Daily structured activities help increase familiarity and slow the progression of memory What Services and Amenities Do Memory Homes Offer? Like assisted living communities, memory care homes offer services and amenities to help in the activities of daily This means there is a prevalent support system to help residents with personal care such as eating, bathing, getting dressed, toileting, medication management, and other daily Other amenities and conveniences in memory care centers include meals each day, programs and social activities, fitness programs, physical therapy, housekeeping, and We Are Here To Help If your family member or loved one suffers from Alzheimer’s disease or dementia, Senior Care Center’s personal advisors want to help you find the right memory care home where your loved one can thrive and feel Our advisors want to help you find a home that is perfectly suited for your loved one’s We’ll also help you explore any options, accommodations, and programs to meet your financial Call us now at (866) to set up a appointment with a personal We’ll walk you through the process and address all your concerns and We can also help you set up tours for each community you are interested in Our advisors are here to help you explore every possibility and option and will help you examine the advantages of each Senior Care Center is happy to counsel you through the process of selecting the right home for your Get FREE Senior Care Options for Your Family! CloQ About How it works Impact Customer Experience Media Contact SIMPLIFYING PERSONAL CREDIT CloQ provides cheaper and easy to reach mobile formal to the and unbanked About model Our clientele cannot provide enough, if any, financial data to evaluate their credit We built a credit model that evaluates clients based on behavior and reliability, instead of only financial Legal loans for our clients usually only start at multiple times the amount they We provide that meet clients’ needs, starting from USD , at lower interest rates than their Inclusion We combine tech innovation with the principles of microcredit to reach the group of clients that is either ignored or We want to include the population in the formal credit Education We build mutual trust by encouraging people to educate themselves, which allows them to take better financial By doing that, we aim to build a relationship in which our clients improve their own lives and we can provide financial support in that We at CloQ experienced first handedly the impact of financial When loan sharks are the only available option, people get into a dangerous cycle from which it is difficult to CloQ is the affordable and legal alternative for the and unbanked How CloQ works No Bureaucracy Our main competitors are loan sharks down the This means that clients can literally walk outside or make a phone call in order to receive a The process from downloading the app to requesting their first loan takes 7 minutes, and sequential loans can be requested within one We leverage in order to transfer money to our clients and receive it back, which both gives us access to the unbanked population and cuts down on transfer Options that fit The maximum a new client can initially request is quite low (roughly USD equivalent), but this increases as they build a positive track record (up to USD ). This way we can grow with their needs and reduce At the same time, we offer weekly and repayment terms to better match their personal Scalability Given the notional amount of the loans, scalability and low cost are key in order to have a successful By using our app as our main form of communication with the client and using for the payments, we can scale drastically without a significant increase in Keeping defaults low We leverage AI and a credit model based on data to make sure we can trust our clients to On top of that, we keep our process lean and simple, so that CloQ is simply the best option for them, which creates a Finally we use the most successful part of microcredit, the social pressure, to use the strength of communities to keep defaults Impact of CloQ Women CloQ empowers women In rural areas You just need a phone with internet Financial education CloQ breaks the circle of indebtedness Community Communities make individuals stronger In the city Cheaper and better form of credit Financial inclusion We serve the unbanked Customer experience Fábio José “This helps a I needed to buy an uniform for my new job Thank you!” Edvan Luiz “It came to facilitate our lives! FAQs — Brightways About Us Services Testimonials Rates FAQs Contact: call text About Us Services Testimonials Rates FAQs Contact: call text Will you give me advice or tell me what to do? A good therapist doesn’t give advice or tell you what to Our popular media often projects some of the worst examples of Our therapists don’t give advice or tell you what to do in your Therapy is a safe place to share your thoughts, concerns, and ideas where you’re free from being judged or told what to Therapists use their training and experience to help you discover, restore and empower How do I find a good therapist? Finding a good therapist is not always No one therapist is a match for every You need to find a therapist who makes you feel at ease and free to share whatever is on your Checking your therapist’s background (schooling, licensure, supervision, and so on) can help ensure you find a therapist who is a good fit for How often should I come to therapy? We recommend weekly appointments, especially towards the beginning of Some clients prefer to come every other week, and some clients prefer twice a All of these options are During your first appointment, we will talk about what works best for How long will it take before I feel better? Therapy is a science, but it’s not an exact No timetable exists to predict how quickly you will see However, talking about your concerns is the fastest and most effective way to address Periodically, we will review your progress in therapy and determine any remaining challenges standing between you and your Will therapy be difficult or painful? Therapy has both benefits and Possible risks include the experience of uncomfortable feelings (such as sadness, guilt, anxiety, anger, frustration, loneliness, or helplessness) or the recall of unpleasant events in a client s Most individuals report that the benefits outweigh the potential risks: a reduction in feelings of distress, better relationships, better and coping skills, and resolution of specific Given the nature of therapy, it is difficult to predict what exactly will happen, but we are committed to making sure our clients are able to handle the risks and experience the Isn t therapy only for people with serious problems or mental illness? Not at We believe all people can benefit from some form of When you’re sad, depressed, anxious or experiencing problems in relationships, it negatively affects many aspects of our lives, such as sleep, physical health and work Mental health has been long overlooked and misunderstood as only for “crazy” Studies have shown that 1 out of every 5 people will experience some form of a mental health problem in their It is only now being understood and appreciated as a critical component for overall Back to Top Falcon Crest Drive, Suite , Redmond, OR About Us | Services | Testimonials | Rates | FAQs | Contact Us All content © Brightways Counseling   Services — Brightways About Us Services Testimonials Rates FAQs Contact: call text About Us Services Testimonials Rates FAQs Contact: call text Our Approach Every person faces challenging circumstances throughout life, but no one has to endure the pain of difficult experiences We know from experience that therapy can be transformative and offers the potential for enormous growth and positive All of our therapy techniques are used to achieve either internal change or external We achieve internal change by processing emotions, beliefs and events that are connected to current We achieve external change by exploring life changes, skills development and the motivation to achieve We believe that all change can be Services Provided to Teens and Adults: - Individual counseling and psychotherapy for improved mood, behavior and life - EMDR for adolescents and adults to treat anxiety, fear, anger, grief loss as well as complex - Attachment Based Family Therapy (ABFT) to help teens struggling with depression, anger, isolation, conflict, low - Nutrition Facts Panel Will be generated from the testing results and will be in line with the new labeling Servings The number of “servings per container” and the “Serving Size” declaration have increased and are now in larger and or bolder Serving sizes have been updated to reflect what people actually eat and drink For example, the serving size for ice cream was previously 1 2 cup and now is 2 3 There are also new requirements for certain size packages, such as those that are between one and two servings or are larger than a single serving but could be consumed in one or multiple Calories “Calories” is now larger and bolder Fats “Calories from Fat” has been removed because research shows the type of fat consumed is more important than the Added Sugars “Added Sugars” in grams and as a percent Daily Value (%DV) is now required on the Added sugars includes sugars that are either added during the processing of foods, or are packaged as such (e.g., a bag of table sugar), and also includes sugars from syrups and honey, and sugars from concentrated fruit or vegetable Scientific data shows that it is difficult to meet nutrient needs while staying within calorie limits if you consume more than percent of your total daily calories from added Nutrients The lists of nutrients that are required or permitted on the label have been Vitamin D and potassium are now required on the label because Americans do not always get the recommended Vitamins A and C are no longer required since deficiencies of these vitamins are rare The actual amount (in milligrams or micrograms) in addition to the %DV must be listed for vitamin D, calcium, iron, and The daily values for nutrients have also been updated based on newer scientific The daily values are reference amounts of nutrients to consume or not to exceed and are used to calculate the %DV. Home - Amprologix : Amprologix Amprologix is developing a portfolio of novel antibiotics derived from naturally occurring antimicrobial peptides (AMPs). Antibiotic Resistance The World Health Organization has warned in that “antibiotic resistance is one of the biggest threats to global health, food security, and development today” and they have published a list of priority pathogens for which new antibiotics are urgently The O’Neill Review on Antimicrobial Resistance (AMR), published in , estimated that by , the global cost of antibiotic resistance will rise to US$100 trillion and drug resistant infections will cause million deaths a year, eclipsing the current toll from cancer and diabetes There is an urgent need for new antibiotics to combat the growing threat of Amprologix is pioneering a family of new antibiotics to meet this Our Technology Our lead compound, NI01, is a potent bactericidal peptide with promising efficacy and toxicity profiles for topical use against bacteria that are on the WHO list of priority In an animal model for methicillin resistant Staphylococcus aureus ( MRSA ) decolonisation, NI01 shows key advantages over the current ‘gold standard’ antibiotic treatment (mupirocin). Minor modifications to the NI01 sequence have generated a family of novel therapeutics with a wide range of potent yet antibacterial This ‘NI01-family’ represents an entirely new class of antibiotic drugs with no known resistance Insights gained from this structure activity data are guiding the development of a pipeline of novel biologics, which include previously unknown AMPs from Our Team The company’s CEO is Gordon Barker, a serial biotech entrepreneur with a track record in company R&D is headed by CSO Prof Mat Upton, a leading microbiologist at the University of Plymouth and discoverer of the NI01 compound More Information For more information on our research, please get in touch with
